================================================================================

Y4 is the Type-1 host hypervisor designed to run WaveTensor accelerator
boards across all commercial form factors (server-farm host A,
special-purpose laptop, rack-mount node, handheld+dock unit, embedded
SoC/SoM). Architecture rationale, base-OS reuse policy, IPC and allocator
fusion model, formal-verification stance, and bootloader selection are
documented in `docs/architecture.md` (canonical) and were originally drafted
under the WaveTensor project as `host_a_custom_hypervisor.md`.

================================================================================

Bases that Y4 reuses (each shipping under its own license; not redistributed
in this repository — pulled in via `third_party/` submodules):

  * seL4 microkernel       https://sel4.systems/
                           (BSD-2-Clause, formally verified)
  * Tock OS (capsule model) https://tockos.org/
                           (MIT OR Apache-2.0)
  * DragonFlyBSD (LWKT, vkernel components)
                           https://www.dragonflybsd.org/
                           (BSD-3-Clause)
  * Redox OS (scheme IPC, relibc, kernel core crates)
                           https://www.redox-os.org/
                           (MIT)
  * Limine bootloader      https://limine-bootloader.org/
                           (BSD-2-Clause) — primary bootloader

Verification toolchain (build-time, not redistributed):

  * Verus                  https://verus-lang.github.io/verus/
                           (MIT)
  * Coq / Rocq             https://coq.inria.fr/
                           (LGPL-2.1)
  * Kani                   https://model-checking.github.io/kani/
                           (Apache-2.0 OR MIT)

